Looking at the code, I can see the issue clearly. In the `PrepublishingHomeViewModel.kt` file, at lines 115-135, there's logic that should hide the categories UI for pages but it's not working correctly.

The problem is in lines 115-119:
```kotlin
if (!editPostRepository.isPage) {
    showNotSetPost(editPostRepository, site)
} else {
    UiStringRes(R.string.prepublishing_nudges_home_categories_not_set)
}
```

This if-else block checks if it's NOT a page (`!editPostRepository.isPage`), and if so, calls `showNotSetPost` which adds Tags. The else branch (when it IS a page) doesn't actually do anything useful with the UiStringRes - it just creates it but doesn't use it.

Then, lines 121-135 ALWAYS add the Categories UI regardless of whether it's a page or post:
```kotlin
val categoriesString = getCategoriesUseCase.getPostCategoriesString(
    editPostRepository,
    site
)

add(HomeUiState(
    navigationAction = PrepublishingScreenNavigation.Categories,
    actionResult = if (categoriesString.isNotEmpty()) {
        UiStringText(categoriesString)
    } else {
        run { UiStringRes(R.string.prepublishing_nudges_home_categories_not_set) }
    },
    actionClickable = true,
    onNavigationActionClicked = ::onActionClicked
))
```

This code should only be executed for posts, not for pages. The fix is to wrap this block inside the `if (!editPostRepository.isPage)` condition.

